<br>
There are three (possibly four) big problems to overcome.<br>
<br>
1)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Concealing her construction.<br>
2)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Concealing her deployment<br>
3)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Concealing (or even being capable of) the production of pulse units<br>
4)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp (The possible fourth!) Keeping a big project secret!<br>
<br>
I address each in turn;<br>
<br>
1)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp A rocket looks like a rocket! An Orion looks like a building! The original design concept for Orion was simply a hemisphere. From a satellite or spy plane she would just look like a dome. No problems there!<br>
2)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp For a clandestine project, I envisage building the Orion at a shipyard. She would be built to look like a shore facility or factory. It would only be when launch was imminent that she would be taken out to sea on a barge for launching.<br>
3)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I think this is actually the hardest bit. There are many members of the Nuclear club these days, Most I wouldn’t trust with a box of matches, let alone Nuclear explosives! &gt;8-O!. However there are only 5, (Possibly even only 4, I’m really not that sure about China) who have the capability and resources to manufacture the 2-3000 small bombs that would be needed for the pulse units for an Orion mission. (We all know who we are! 8-))!  )<br>
4)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hmm, Keeping it secret. Building the pulse units wouldn’t be a problem (Assuming you have the capability in the first place, see 3 above!). Building the ship would be. We’re not talking rocket science here. We’re talking “heavy” engineering. The kind of workforce that would be needed would have to be recruited from people who would not be used to a culture of working in secrecy and we (Oops, Freudian slip! J ) may have some difficulty in maintaining security.( &lt;FX:Scenario&gt; &lt;Hard Mech, Eng.10.30pm, Friday night, drunk as skunk&gt; “Hello friend, what do you do? (Reply) “I build spashippssz powreerdsh by atom bomshh” )  Mind you, huge projects have been achieved in complete secrecy before (Manhattan project, Tube alloys etc) so perhaps its not insurmountable.<br>
<br>
One couldn’t launch secretly (Who’d want to, I’d invite various world leaders to “ a party you’ll never forget” and challenge them afterwards to “Top that if you can!”)  but building and deploying is definitely possible<br>
<br>
Dusty<br>
